(533, '', NULL, '<h2><em>Shop Union and Patronize Union Workplaces.&nbsp;</em></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://ufcw648.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Screen-Shot-2014-03-20-at-5.47.08-PM.png" style="width: 280px; height: 100px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div id="hdr" style="font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: 20.7999992370605px; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; outline: none; border-width: 10px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(0, 37, 87); font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; overflow: hidden; background: rgb(0, 73, 144);">\r\n<header class="wrapper" id="hdr-content" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; outline: none; max-width: 980px;">\r\n<h1 class="pagetitle" style="line-height: 1em; margin: 0px 12px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; border: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova-condensed, proxima-nova, ''Proxima Nova'', HelveticaNeue, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1.875em; vertical-align: baseline; font-stretch: normal; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); float: left;">Shop Union</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="post" style="font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: 20.7999992370605px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<div class="entry" style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px 0px 1.5em; outline: none; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<h2 style="line-height: 1em; margin: 20px 0px 10px; padding: 18px 0px 10px 20px; outline: none; border-width: 10px 0px 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-top-color: rgb(255, 196, 37); border-bottom-color: rgb(0, 73, 144); font-family: proxima-nova-condensed, proxima-nova, ''Proxima Nova'', HelveticaNeue, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1.875em; vertical-align: baseline; font-stretch: normal; color: rgb(0, 73, 144); min-height: 30px; background-image: url(http://www.ufcw.org/wp-content/themes/ufcw/images/bg_hdr.png); background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0% 22px; background-repeat: no-repeat;">Work Union. Shop Union. Stronger Communities</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>When you choose to patronize a union workplace, you are making a choice to support your community and a better quality of life for the people who live there. By having a voice in the workplace, union members can improve working conditions for ourselves and the people we serve every day. Grocery and Meat Retail Health Care Printing Other Industries Why Patronizing Union Matters Union members, on average get paid more in wages, get better health benefits, vacation, sick leave and retirement plan than non-union members. And union members have a contract with their employer that helps protects them from favoritism and unjust treatment on the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a customer or patient, where you choose to spend your money and get your health care sends a message. Thank you for choosing a union workplace when shopping. It makes a difference. Promote your union workplace or business Do you want to promote your union shop in the San Francisco area? Please contact Local 5 by email at <a href="mailto:ufcwsj@gmail.com">ufcwsj@gmail.com</a>. We are happy to list all union businesses on our website for free. For paid listings or advertising promotions, email for details. Work Union, Shop Union, Live Union!</p>\r\n', '', '2015-03-24 15:06:13', '2.5', 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 1),
(534, 'What is SCBTC ?', NULL, 'For decades in Santa Clara and San Benito County, the Building & Construction Trades Council has been the driving force for excellence in the construction industry in the bay area.\r\n\r\nThe twenty-three craft unions affiliated with the council represent over 30,000 highly trained, skilled construction industry workers employed in Silicon Valley.\r\n\r\nThrough the efforts of the Building Trades Council, Silicon Valley has enjoyed the highest level of professionalism and training in step with the increasingly demanding requirements of the region''s high technology companies and developers. \r\n\r\nUnion crafts people are twenty-nine percent more productive than or non-union counterparts.\r\nFor a job done on time, at budget and the best quality, build it union.', '', '2015-02-17 08:13:45', '10.1', 3, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
