(588, '', NULL, '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);"><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/P7250022-e1426700093417.jpg" style="height: 210px; width: 280px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">United Food and Commercial Workers Local 480&nbsp;is a 2,500 member labor union based in Honolulu, Hawaii. The local is a progressive voice in the labor movement and the community with a strong tradition of member advocacy and involvement. It is an affiliate of the United Food and Commercial Workers International union based in Washington DC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480&nbsp;members work primarily in retail grocery and meat and in nursing homes,&nbsp;retail drug stores, agriculture and food processing, wholesale meat, seafood processing,&nbsp;and in the industry of education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Wherever Local 480&nbsp;members work, they have a strong voice on the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480&nbsp;policy is set by its&nbsp;member executive board which consists of its elected officers and rank and file members. Members from many of the Hawaiian Islands&nbsp;sit on its board. The activism of the board and the union&rsquo;s membership assures the democratic nature of the organization and perpetuate its progressive tradition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480 is a Union Preparing Today for the Needs of its Members Tomorrow.</p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-04 08:35:11', '40.1', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1),
(589, 'Hawaii Dental Group', NULL, '<p>In our continual effort to provide added benefits and value to our membership, we have found a dental office that is willing to save our members money on their dental services at their offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A 20% discount or no out of pocket expenses when you are seen at Hawaii Dental Offices. (depending on your plan coverage, not exceeding the maximum plan benefit and provided you have coverage for the month of services) &nbsp; Visit one of the preferred dental offices and you will receive these savings just for being a member of UFCW Local 480.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="style2" p="" style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);"><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-04-27-at-2.35.41-PM.png" style="width: 280px; height: 78px;" />‚Äã</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="style2">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-04 09:58:06', '49', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1),
(590, 'Negotiations Updates for Foodland, Foodland Farms and Sack n Save', NULL, '<p>This is your union president Pat Loo with a negotiation update message from your union for our members working at Foodland, Foodland Farms and Sack N Save.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your union has secured your benefits and wages by signing an extension agreement with your employer Foodland.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your contract will remain in effect until a new agreement is reached.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ongoing economic crisis healthcare issues and pension uncertainty has made lengthy negotiations a reality--Not only for our union but most others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Union has&nbsp;scheduled meetings with your employer in May&nbsp;and we expect to negotiate well into June.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once again, your union contract is in effect and your benefits are secure. There is no reason to rush the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your union will continue to communicate with this new technology to keep you up-to-date on the progress in negotiations. Stay informed, get involved and help keep your contract and union strong.&nbsp;Thank you for your participation and your ongoing support for your union!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pat Loo, President</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-04-27-at-2.35.41-PM.png" style="width: 280px; height: 78px;" /></p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-14 06:43:02', '46', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1),
(591, 'Update on HB 321', NULL, '<p>THE 2015 LEGISLATIVE SESSION<br />\r\nUpdate on HB321 HD1 SD2 (The Dispensary Bill): CONFERENCE COMMITTEE (with new Senate Chair) will reconvene for the last time on Monday, May 4th at NOON, Room 229.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><a href="http://www.capitol.hawaii.gov/session2015/hearingnotices/CONF_PSM_05-04-15_C_.HTM">Click for HEARING NOTICE.</a></strong><br />\r\nWhat Happened? Read Civil Beat&#39;s account <strong><a href="http://www.civilbeat.com/2015/05/hawaii-legislature-may-resurrect-bill-to-establish-marijuana-dispensaries/">HERE.</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PLEASE NOTE: NO TESTIMONY IS ACCEPTED DURING CONFERENCE COMMITTEE meetings.<br />\r\nSB1291(SD2)The Civil Protections bill has PASSED through all committees! Next step: Full Floor Vote. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n2015 legislative session began on January 21st 2015. This is likely to be a very big year for medical marijuana. We have collected a list of the bills, with short summaries and the latest updates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Click on the BILL number to be taken to the legislature&rsquo;s website to read the text and register to receive up-to-the-minute information about the bill.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To receive our periodic action alerts and updates, please sign up for our mailing list.</p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-04 10:05:25', '47', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1),
(592, '', NULL, '<p><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/P7250072.jpg" style="width: 280px; height: 210px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unions are about a simple proposition: By joining together, working women and men gain strength in numbers so they can have a voice at work about what they care about.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They negotiate a contract with their employer for things like a fair and safe workplace, better wages, a secure retirement and family-friendly policies such as paid sick leave and scheduling hours. They have a voice in how their jobs get done, creating a more stable, productive workforce that provides better services and products. Always adapting to the challenges of our nation&rsquo;s evolving workforce, unions are meeting the needs of workers in today&rsquo;s flexible and nontraditional work environments. Because no matter what type of job workers are in, by building power in unions, they can speak out for fairness for all working people in their communities and create better standards and a strong middle class across the country.</p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-04 08:45:38', '40.2', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1),
(593, '', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-04-at-9.50.19-AM.png" style="width: 280px; height: 210px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">Working people from all walks of life join together in unions to obtain a voice at work. Union members have a say about pay, benefits, working conditions and how their jobs get done.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you do not have a union at your job, find out more about how to form one. Today, more people are taking the step to form unions on the job than at any time in recent history. You can be one of them!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Call UFCW Local 480 at&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">(808) 942.7778 or email us at ufcwlocal480@gmail.com to get more information. &nbsp;Just ask to speak with someone in our organizing department and they will be happy to help you get started.</span></p>\r\n', '', '2015-05-04 08:53:28', '40.3', 6, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 1);
